&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Seeing the Lion charging at him only made Trelos more thirsty for blood.
 His already-fast pace turning to frantic as he made dog-like growls and
snorts.  As he got within range, he lept into the air with his powerful hind
legs and attempting to bite down on any part of his enemy that he could get
ahold of.

&lt;NEW&gt;

The Mecha-lion had been running towards Trelos, so as he watched him leap
into the air, he also followed suit. Powerful hind legs, like the steel
springs that were housed within them, pushed the lion into the air, as he
extended his claws and bared his teeth, the sound in his chest reverberating
as much as like a motor as it did the growl that it was!

{RROOAARR!!}

The meeting was titanic and yet painful!! As armored as the lion-like
cybertronian was, it was obvious that he was also recovering from some sort
of grievous injury of his own, and there were placed where his armor was not
as strong as it could have been. Unfortunately it was one of these places
that Trelos found and bit down on. So the roar that had sounded was one of
pain as much as it was one of challenge!

With the pain, it was as if something awoke in the optics of the armored
lion, optics blinked and flickered as some sort of intelligence began to
look out of them, something more than the bestial anger and reflexes that
had been there before.

With another roar of challenge the great cat flexed his neck and back as he
opened great powerful jaws and, for a moment, exposing dark metallic teeth
which glinted in the light! Turning his neck and head he lunged downward to
bite down on the canine!

&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Meanwhile....
&gt;
&gt; The two Maximals were about to retreat when they noticed that the two
enemies were no longer interested in them.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Depthcharge to base.  It looks like the two enemies have transformed back
into beast mode and are fighting each other.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Interesting.&quot; replied Salveo. &quot;Bossman still wants you to retreat.
Ravenchief, please leave a spypod on that building.  We can probably use an
eye on that building.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; Ravenchief planted the small pod then keyed his radio.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;At the very least, we&#39;ll have something interesting to watch tonight.
Start recording!  We&#39;ll be back soon.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; And with that, the two of them jumped off the backside of the building and
took to the air.

&lt;NEW&gt;

 There was no evidence of thought or attention given to Depthcharge or
Ravenchief above, there was only battle and pain and anger! The momentary
intelligence that had appeared had been seemingly lulled, or perhaps forced,
back to sleep by the savage ferocity of the battle

OOC: I am not sure if you mean Trelos transformed or if Trelos AND the lion
transformed, but please keep in mind the lion has never assumed robot mode
or even spoken since the Maximals have seen him.  Also he seems to be
reacting on an almost instinctual level for the most part. Do with that
knowedge what you will.

